question:
District category contains Gated Community, Manufacturing District, and Single-family Homes.
Supermarkets category contains Wegmans, Aldi, and Earth Fare.
The number of each Gated Community 's Aldi equals 20 times the sum of each Single-family Homes 's Aldi, each Single-family Homes 's Supermarkets, and each Gated Community 's Wegmans.
The number of each Manufacturing District 's Aldi equals 19 times each Manufacturing District 's Wegmans.
The number of each Gated Community 's Wegmans equals 9 more than the sum of each Single-family Homes 's Supermarkets and each Single-family Homes 's Aldi.
The number of each Manufacturing District 's Earth Fare equals the difference of each Gated Community 's Earth Fare and each Single-family Homes 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Gated Community 's Earth Fare equals 1 more than the sum of each Gated Community 's Aldi, each Single-family Homes 's Aldi, and each Gated Community 's Wegmans.
The number of each Single-family Homes 's Aldi equals 12.
The number of each Manufacturing District 's Wegmans equals 16.
How many Supermarkets does Gated Community have?
solution:
Define each Single-family Homes 's Aldi as a; So a = 12.
Define each Single-family Homes 's Supermarkets as O; So O = a = 12.
Define each Gated Community 's Wegmans as H; P = O + a = 12 + 12 = 1; So H = 9 + P = 9 + 1 = 10.
Define each Gated Community 's Aldi as u; c = H + O = 10 + 12 = 22; t = a + c = 12 + 22 = 11; So u = 20 * t = 20 * 11 = 13.
Define each Gated Community 's Earth Fare as v; y = a + H = 12 + 10 = 22; Y = u + y = 13 + 22 = 12; So v = 1 + Y = 1 + 12 = 13.
Define each Gated Community 's Supermarkets as W; X = v + H = 13 + 10 = 0; So W = u + X = 13 + 0 = 13.
